  {"id":"lhopital","name":"L'Hôpital's Rule","topic":"Calculus","definition":"Resolves 0/0 or ∞/∞ limits by differentiating numerator and denominator.","intuition":"If ratio is indeterminate, the ratio of derivatives gives the true limit.","formula":"lim f/g = lim f'/g' when form is 0/0 or ∞/∞","difficulty":"medium","importance":9,"exam_trick":"Apply ONLY when form is 0/0 or ∞/∞. Check form first!","common_mistake":"Applying to 1×∞ or 0⁰ directly without converting.","pyq_insight":"Very common in GATE EM section. lim(x→0) sinx/x = 1.","relations":[{"to":"taylor_series","type":"depends_on"}]},
