  {"id":"newton_leibnitz","name":"Newton-Leibnitz Rule","topic":"Calculus","definition":"Differentiates a definite integral with variable limits.","intuition":"Chain rule applied to each boundary of the integral.","formula":"d/dx[∫φ^ψ f(t)dt] = f(ψ)ψ' - f(φ)φ'","difficulty":"hard","importance":9,"exam_trick":"Use when limit question has integral in numerator/denominator.","common_mistake":"Forgetting to multiply by derivative of the limit bound.","pyq_insight":"Very high frequency 2-mark GATE question combined with L'Hôpital.","relations":[]},
